detaileddescription.para: This declares a list of tokens that can be used globally. Use in conjunction with TF_DEFINE_PUBLIC_TOKENS.

briefdescription.para: This file defines some macros that are useful for declaring and using static TfTokens.

detaileddescription.para: Typically, using static TfTokens is either cumbersome, unsafe, or slow. These macros aim to solve many of the common problems.

There are PUBLIC and PRIVATE versions of the macros. The PRIVATE ones are intended to be used when the tokens will only be used in a single .cpp file, in which case they can be made file static. In the case of the PRIVATE, you only need to use the DEFINE macro.
